<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD0C5A25FF7AFCB3C804CDE6" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD0C5A25FF7AFCB3CE69CD7C" blockId="14.[227,591,796,822]" box="[227,591,796,822]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD0C5A25FF7AFCB3CE69CD7C" bold="true" box="[227,591,796,822]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF7AFCB3CE69CD7C" bold="true" box="[227,591,796,822]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description of colour pattern</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD0C5A25FF7AFCE4C804CDE6" blockId="14.[227,1438,843,940]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">The colour pattern consists of closely related, delicate, elongated, wavy spiral rows of dashes. On the spires, the pattern consists of very thin axial flammulae, closely related to each other. The flammulae are vaguely connected with a spiral band, at the center of the sutural ramp.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD0C5A25FF7AFC7CCE73CBC8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD0C5A25FF7AFC7CCD73CDA7" blockId="14.[227,341,979,1005]" box="[227,341,979,1005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD0C5A25FF7AFC7CCD73CDA7" bold="true" box="[227,341,979,1005]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF7AFC7CCD73CDA7" bold="true" box="[227,341,979,1005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD0C5A25FF7AFBAECE16CB58" blockId="14.[227,1437,1025,1298]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species is very similar in morphology (
<tableCitation id="2B030321DD0C5A25FD63FBAECF70CA51" box="[762,854,1025,1051]" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="14.[227,296,303,329]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Table 3. Shell measurements of one broken specimen of Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 1 (MNHN.F.A82982) from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece)." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Table 3</tableCitation>
) to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FC12FBAEC8E4CA51" authority="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou, 2022" authorityName="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou" authorityYear="2022" box="[907,1218,1025,1052]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ictini" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FC12FBAECFF0CA51" box="[907,982,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FC73FBADC855CA51" box="[1002,1139,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lautoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FB1FFBADC8E4CA51" box="[1158,1218,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ictini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4FC657F3DD0C5A25FB54FBADC90CCA56" box="[1229,1322,1026,1052]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It differs in the wider shoulder and the relatively lower conical spire outline. It can also be distinguished by its relatively shallower subsutural flexure relative depth (SSFd = 
<quantity id="A1799B7FDD0C5A25FB98FBE7C871CA2B" box="[1025,1111,1095,1122]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23952" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="4.88">4.88 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FBFBFBE7C9BACA2B" authority="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou, 2022" authorityName="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou" authorityYear="2022" box="[1122,1436,1096,1122]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ictini" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FBFBFBE7C88BCA28" box="[1122,1197,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FB5BFBE7C96DCA2B" box="[1218,1355,1096,1121]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lautoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FAF9FBE7C9BACA2B" box="[1376,1436,1096,1121]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ictini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4FC657F3DD0C5A25FF7AFBC4CD63CACF" box="[227,325,1131,1157]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Moreover, it displays a very different colour pattern from the brick-like pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FAC8FBC4CDE2CAE2" authority="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou, 2022" authorityName="Psarras &amp; Merle &amp; Koskeridou" authorityYear="2022" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ictini" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FAC8FBC4C9BACACF" box="[1361,1436,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF74FB20CD50CAE2" box="[237,374,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lautoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FE11FB20CDE2CAE2" box="[392,452,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ictini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4FC657F3DD0C5A25FE54FB21CE0ECAE2" box="[461,552,1166,1192]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD0C5A25FDA0FB21CEA4CAE3" box="[569,642,1166,1193]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[227,270,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[264,1398,741,1964]" captionTargetId="figure-103@13.[264,1398,741,1964]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 1 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece), specimen MNHN.F.A82982, in abapertural and apical views, under natural (A2) and UV light. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484275/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Another species with a similar colour pattern on the last whorl is 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FF7DFB1ECF54CA81" authority="Hoernes &amp; Auinger, 1879" authorityName="Hoernes &amp; Auinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[228,882,1201,1228]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="suessi" subGenus="Leporiconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF7DFB1ECD09CA81" box="[228,303,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FEDBFB1DCDF3CA81" box="[322,469,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Leporiconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FE70FB1DCE09CA81" box="[489,559,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">suessi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD0C5A25FDA3FB1DCF54CA81" author="Hoernes R. &amp; Auinger M." box="[570,882,1201,1228]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref29927" refString="Hoernes R. &amp; Auinger M. 1879. Die Gasteropoden der Meeres-Ablagerungen der ersten und zweiten Miocanen Mediterran-Stufe in der Osterreichisch-Ungarischen Monarchie. Abhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Geologischen Reichsanstalt 12: 1 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 151405" type="journal article" year="1879">Hoernes &amp; Auinger, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD0C5A25FC2FFB1EC92CCA86" author="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B." box="[950,1290,1201,1228]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref29682" refString="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B. 2016. A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 1 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau 2016</bibRefCitation>
), but 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FAC8FB1ECD59CAA5" authority="" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1923" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FAC8FB1EC9BACA81" box="[1361,1436,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF74FB7ACD50CAA4" box="[237,374,1237,1262]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lautoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1 does not possess striate spire whorls. Therefore, it does not match the description of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD0C5A25FF7AFB57CE0FCB5B" authorityName="Hoernes &amp; Auinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[227,553,1272,1298]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="suessi" subGenus="Leporiconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FF7AFB57CD08CB58" box="[227,302,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FEA6FB57CDF4CB5B" box="[319,466,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Leporiconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD0C5A25FE7AFB57CE0FCB5B" box="[483,553,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">suessi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
